LogFile.FinalText: Some people maintain that men and women speak two different languages. If a man in a relationship says that he does not want to talk about his problems the typical woman feels that he does not include her in his world. If the woman says to him that she does not want to talk about the problems most men believe that she does not need to talk about them. These misunderstandings cause quarrels. When big quarrels arise women and men also act differently. New research shows that many women cry when they are angry. In these situations intimidated men chose to run away and they can feel helpless. In contrast to the crying woman the angry man uses harsh words. Despite these different reactions most men and women live together peacefully and quite frankly we cannot live without each other.
